GEMINI-CURSES(1)           User Commands           GEMINI-CURSES(1)

NAME
    gemini-curses - full-screen ncurses Gemini chat client for the terminal

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-curses
    gemini-curses <session_name>
    gemini-curses --resume <session_name>
    gemini-curses --list
    gemini-curses --models
    gemini-curses --update-models
    gemini-curses --test-model <model_id>
    gemini-curses --doctor
    gemini-curses --version
    gemini-curses --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-curses is the Python ncurses implementation of the
    gemini-terminal-tools project.  It is a full-screen text terminal chat
    client for the Gemini API.

    The project goal is to provide a user-friendly and robust chat client in
    the terminal.  Browsers and browser interfaces are not required for
    sending text messages and attachments back and forth to an AI.

    gemini-curses provides:
        - scrollable transcript window
        - wrapped multiline input
        - clickable command strip
        - global function-key navigation
        - mousewheel scrolling
        - model discovery using cached listModels metadata
        - user-operated model testing
        - API-key manager
        - session browser and rename support
        - w3m-style options form
        - memory viewer/editor
        - file and attachment browser
        - local file attachments
        - returned inlineData attachment saving
        - external editor support
        - startup Project Lead notice
        - diagnostics / doctor report

USAGE
    First-time setup from inside the interface:

        gemini-curses
            Press F3 to paste an API key.
            Press F2 to load or update the model list.
            Select and test a model.

    Start a normal timestamped chat:

        gemini-curses

    Start a named full-screen chat:

        gemini-curses android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        gemini-curses --resume android-backup

    List saved chats:

        gemini-curses --list

    Show cached or fetched model list:

        gemini-curses --models

    Refresh model-list cache from Google:

        gemini-curses --update-models

    Test one model from the shell:

        gemini-curses --test-model gemini-2.5-flash

    Run diagnostics:

        gemini-curses --doctor

SESSION MANAGEMENT
    gemini-curses
        Start a new timestamped session.

    gemini-curses <name>
        Start or open a named session.

    gemini-curses --resume <name>
        Resume an existing named session.  If the session does not exist, the
        command exits with an error.

    gemini-curses --list
        List saved sessions.

    F4
        Open the session browser.  The session browser can open an existing
        session, start a new timestamped session, or rename the current
        session.

