GLOBAL FUNCTION-KEY NAVIGATION
    Function keys are intended to work across feature screens.  If the user
    opens F3 accidentally, pressing F2, F4, F5, F6, F7, F8, or F9 should jump
    directly to that feature instead of requiring Esc first.

    This behavior is part of the usability contract for the Python ncurses
    reference implementation and should be preserved in future implementations.

MOUSE SUPPORT
    Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support for ncurses mouse
    events.

    Main chat view:

        Mouse wheel up/down
            Scroll transcript.

        Left click in input area
            Place the input cursor near the clicked position.

        Left click visible command label
            Launch that feature.

    Lists and selectors:

        Mouse wheel up/down
            Scroll list rows.

        Left click row
            Highlight or select row.

        Double click row
            Activate row where supported.

    Drag selection belongs to the terminal emulator and is not implemented by
    gemini-curses.

MODEL DISCOVERY
    Available Gemini models can be listed from the command line:

        gemini-curses --models

    The model cache can be refreshed explicitly:

        gemini-curses --update-models

    They can also be listed directly with curl:

        curl "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_API_KEY"

    Inside the ncurses interface, press F2.  F2 opens a local model menu first;
    it does not contact Google until the user explicitly chooses to load or
    update the model list.

MODEL FILTERING
    gemini-curses uses model metadata returned by the models endpoint.  The
    selector can filter models by:

        - generateContent support
        - nonzero input/output token limits
        - preview/experimental name patterns
        - minimum input token limit
        - minimum output token limit

    This metadata-driven workflow is preferred over probing every model.

MODEL TESTING
    Autoscan is not used.  The user selects one model and may test that model.

    In the model selector:

        t
            Test the highlighted model.

    From the shell:

        gemini-curses --test-model <model_id>

    The tester sends MODEL_TEST_PROMPT to the selected model and displays the
    raw response.  The user decides whether to activate or save the model.

DIAGNOSTICS
    Diagnostics can be run from the shell:

        gemini-curses --doctor

    Diagnostics can also be opened from the F1 command menu with D.

    The doctor report checks:
        - program version
        - Python version
        - curses availability
        - TERM
        - terminal size
        - API-key presence
        - session directory writability
        - attachment directory writability
        - model-cache directory writability
        - config-file visibility
        - model-cache state
        - external editor resolution
        - DNS resolution for the Gemini API host

    The doctor report does not print API-key values.  It does not call
    generateContent.  It does not update the model cache; use --update-models
    for that.

CONFIGURATION
    Configuration file:

        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    Format:

        KEY=VALUE

    Supported keys include:

        MODEL
            Gemini model identifier.

        CONTEXT_TURNS
            Number of recent user/assistant exchanges sent back to Gemini as
            conversation context.

        HISTORY_LIMIT
            Legacy alias for CONTEXT_TURNS.

        GEMINI_API_KEY
            Optional API key.  Environment variable takes priority.

        SESSION_DIR
            Directory used for session log storage.

        ATTACHMENT_DIR
            Directory used for extracted code artifacts and returned inline
            attachments.

        EDITOR
            External editor command.

        MODEL_TEST_PROMPT
            Prompt sent by the model tester.

        MODEL_CACHE_FILE
            Path to cached model-list JSON.

        MODEL_FILTER_GENERATE_CONTENT
            Require generateContent support.

        MODEL_FILTER_REQUIRE_TOKENS
            Require nonzero token-limit metadata.

        MODEL_FILTER_HIDE_PREVIEW
            Hide preview/experimental/beta model names.

        MODEL_MIN_INPUT_TOKENS
            Minimum input token limit.

        MODEL_MIN_OUTPUT_TOKENS
            Minimum output token limit.

        MODEL_SORT_ORDER
            Sort order for model display.

        INPUT_PLACEHOLDER
            Placeholder text shown in the empty input field.

        MONOCHROME
            Disable grey/dim-dependent styling.

        STARTUP_NOTICE
            Enable or disable Project Lead startup notice.

ENVIRONMENT
    GEMINI_API_KEY
        Preferred API key source.

        Precedence:
            1. Environment variable
            2. Config file
            3. F3 runtime API-key input

    VISUAL
    EDITOR
        Used for external editor support if EDITOR is not set in config.

FILES
    ~/.config/gemini-cli/config
        Configuration file.

    SESSION_DIR/*.log
        Session log files.

    ATTACHMENT_DIR/
        Extracted code block attachments, generated inlineData attachments,
        and other saved artifacts.

    MODEL_CACHE_FILE
        Cached model-list JSON.

ATTACHMENT SYSTEM
    Code blocks returned by Gemini are extracted from terminal display and
    saved into ATTACHMENT_DIR.

    Local files can be attached to the next prompt through F7.  Text-like
    files are sent as text parts.  Binary/media files are sent as inlineData
    parts when the Gemini API and selected model support them.

    Generated inlineData parts returned by Gemini are saved into
    ATTACHMENT_DIR when possible.

MEMORY MODEL
    gemini-curses keeps a rolling conversation context in memory.

    CONTEXT_TURNS controls how many recent user/assistant exchanges are sent
    back to Gemini with each request.

    Memory snapshots are written into the session log as system entries.  When
    resuming an existing session, gemini-curses prefers the latest memory
    snapshot and falls back to rebuilding context from recent chat entries.

PROJECT LEAD NOTICE
    In a new blank session, gemini-curses can display a temporary transcript
    message from remfan1994.  The message is removed when the first user
    message is sent.

    The notice is not written to logs, not sent to Gemini, and not stored in
    memory.

EXTERNAL EDITOR
    F8 opens the editor menu.

    Editor selection order:
        1. EDITOR config key
        2. VISUAL environment variable
        3. EDITOR environment variable
        4. common editor detection

LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support
    - Requires internet access for Gemini requests
    - API quota restrictions apply
    - Media attachment support depends on Gemini model/API support
    - Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support
    - Drag selection belongs to the terminal emulator
    - Model testing verifies one selected model, not all models

